- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a new concept for massively scalable computations on streaming data using the Spark computing framework. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for estimating vehicular traffic. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing smartphone traces to estimate traffic in urban networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses controlling and analyzing cyberphysical and robotics systems. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of a cloud-based solution for processing data.
